I regularly stop here for breakfast or lunch. They have a pretty good selection of did at fairly solid prices. They have a hot bar for both breakfast and lunch though that can get pretty expensive. In the morning they have a bagel station and am omlett station. At lunch they have a burger station, taco/burrito station, ramen station, sushi station, salad station, and a deli sandwich station.

The fish was too too salty because of that sauce that they put on top of it. But that was not bad enough, at 2:23pm, they are sweeping the floor while customers are eating. Now they are taking out the trash and transporting it through the eating area while there are many people still eating and the to top it off, one person brought out a mop, a bucket of water and proceeds to mop the floor. I asked one of the men about all this sweeping, cleaning and garbage while customers are eating.  He answered with some annoyance that “yes” that’s what they do here. I’m out! My stomach is not feeling right at this point. First and last time for me! On my way out I spoke with a manager who promised to tell the workers not to do so again. Looks like a habit to me. Hope they break that habit.

The food is really good but the reason I give 3 stars and not 5 is because the value is absolutely terrible, surely for the buffet section, and this is due to very poor organisation. Basically whatever you take from the buffet gets weighted and you get charged according to the weight. This is absolutely unfair as I took only some vegetarian noodles and some spring rolls while my friend took all possible type of meats and got charged the same. There is not distinction whatsoever even from lamb or chicken. That means they weight the food at the most expensive value to cover the most expensive food not taking into account that some food instead is very cheap to buy and it should be sold at a cheaper price (such as beans or vegetables). You could take a whole tray of carrots and get charged exactly as a whole tray of lamb.. So for this reason even though the food is quite nice I don’t recommend eating here.
